      "instruction": "<p>Cut 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> piece<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper, then lay the <strong>green beans </strong>in the middle with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the beans to form sealed parcel<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and put in the oven for 10-12 min or until the beans are tender with a slight bite</p><p>Return the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with the <strong>soft cheese</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>,<strong> </strong>season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
